caption: The amazing food and friendly staff keep me coming back. Even though the waitress was very busy she took the time to make recommendations and I must say they were all outstanding. Spicy fish was excellent as well as dumplings and pork buns! My waitress was excellent!

Amazing food and amazing service!   This place has a variety of traditional Shanghai dishes that makes your restaurant experience exciting!!  If you are up to explore new foods with good service, this place is a must go!!! Sam
The cashier girl was rude. I wanted to ask her to turn on the heater for me. She refused me with a super whatever attitude. DISAPPOINTED.
We had the orange beef with some chow mein and it was very good (especially paired with the Asahi beer). I loved the tiny plate of peanuts they brought while we waited for our food.
Chicken and shrimp chow mein was delicious. Service was great.
While I was half way done with the fried rice, found a hair inside with the rice.

This restaurant gives great service and delicious menu. My favourite place around here. The food and drinks came out rapidly and the rates were economical. Highly recommended.

(Translated by Google) I ordered the spicy stir-fried beef and it turned out to be sweet, and the tofu in it also had a sour taste. The ingredients are not very fresh. It's on Sawtelle.  (Original) 点了辣炒牛肉结果是甜的, 里面配的豆腐也有一股酸味。 The ingredients are not very fresh. It's on Sawtelle.
Great food and service during this Covid-19 pandemic situation
Amazing food, great service. The food has a lot of flavor and I definitely recommend. The people there where very nice
Food ok, bad service. Not once they came to ask if we need it anything else.
Best dry fried chicken we've ever ate!  We LOVE this place.  We come here every time we're in San Francisco.  MUST EAT HERE!!
It’s good, but very greasy and very oily.  Bonus points for actually capturing some of the Szechuan flavors.

They have an efficient system. I ordered wings over the phone while driving to the restaurant. Got em crispy, hot and fresh 20 mins after. Rated it 4 stars over all although the wings were a bit too much on the sweet side for me. We ate the wings on the go. Otherwise it would have been perfect with the black bean noodle or fried rice.

I came here twice and I remember thoroughly enjoying it. I always order the chicken and boy is it delicious! I have tried the string beans, shrimp and leek dumplings, honey walnut shrimp, black bean noodles and of course the fried chicken.

Some dumplings were fantastic, namely the mushroom one, others seemed unsalted. They added someone else's order into my bag so I got to a good variety, overall pretty good but not consistent on flavor quality.

Relatively quick for takeout. During these times of the pandemic, they were super careful with almost no interaction (everything packed up and ready to go). Food was alright – house green beans were overdressed with a thick sauce. Should not be so overcooked. Vegetable dumplings were good.
I want here because I was on a bike ride. My lunch was good the only thing was it was warm not Hot. I think it was warm because pickup only and very slow with social distance deal. I will go back
Excellent food. Staff conscientious

Came in here one night. Thought I’d give them a go since I’m trying to hit up all the different food places on Sawtelle. I was looking for a wide assortment of noodles and after seeing the name Tasty Noodle House, why not? When I sat down …
As good As It Gets but the food overall is good. Not excellent but sure better than average.

Pretty good place for Chinese food. They have a variety of Chinese dishes that isn't easy to find in Los Angeles, so it is nice. Definitely recommend getting the shui jian bao and their cold chicken appetizer.
Decent food

Sitting in the restaurant on a Monday 2pm. I just ordered a wonton soup and pork bums. Didn’t get my food until 50minutes later. I had to take it to go because my lunch hour is over! Food is average. Too expensive for the price, and it’s way too slow.
Service is good.  Food is good but pricey for what it is.  The soup dumplings are small.  I'm from NYC and I'm used to the big ones from Joe's Shanghai.  Not sure if I would come back though
Junk food
Favorite Chinese food in LA. One of my favorite restaurants in LA period.

Good food. Yummy with good variety. Service was quite slow but they said it was because they were short-staffed
Great food and great service. But it is so busy on Sunday night! Go anywhen but Sunday. I Highly recommend it.
The food took so long to prepare and there wasn’t enough servers. The service has deteriorated since the last time I was here and we were quite disappointed to see it went this way.

Very Clean location. 20 Dollars minimum to use your card.  Hard to get parking.  There are many little Asian restaurants and they are all popular therefore to park at the premises will be difficult. The fried rice was satisfactory.   Came during lunch hour.
Come and get a legit Chinese-styled mooncake (September 13th 2019 is the mid-autumn moon festival). Great dishes, but the price is a bit higher.
Awesome food, every time
Not a lot of (or any!) good Chinese restaurants that serve good ol' "sheng jian bao" on the westside. Love the food here. Sometimes can be a bit oily, but overall the food is great.
The food was good, but the service was terrible
Unpleasant customer service with overpriced food.

The food is good. But they service is terrible. The sever come out and ask me for more tips. This is crazy. First time see a sever ask for more tips without any excuse. Just like I owe him money. Please check about your wallet if go to there
Super busy, and long wait times due to place being rather small. Options are typical of cuisine.

Great food and service! The staff are friendly and helpful. Delicious vegetarian/ vegan option and there are full garlic cloves and a crusher on the table
Yummy dumplings, beef noodle soup is that not good here
Delicious
Good food and well portioned for the pricing. Pumpkin pancakes are delicious and the staff is accommodating.
Just not impressed by the food at all. It was really just ok. Would not come back, especially given there are so many other better options around
Best authentic Chinese food in Sawtelle. Sometimes has B ratings and was shut down once.
Bomb
First time visiting this restaurant.  We were pleasantly surprised with how good and flavorful the food was.  Very tasty. I would definitely go back.
Food was good. It need some flavor or spices on some of the dishes we ordered. The service was good. I might give it another try and try other dishes.

Been there twice while I stayed in the area. their xiaolongbao's skin was sicker than my liking, but the meat and soup inside were very tasty. I love their fried rice, hot and sour soup noodle and fried dumpling. The service and price were good, too. My favorite restaurant in this area! Highly recommended!

Nothing outstanding or particularly worth noting. It is pretty typical Chinese food, lots of options to choose from along with some more unique options such as snails and pig ear. Also to note that it does have lamb, which is typically …
The grilled Shanghai pork buns are a must
The shrimp fried rice was awesome!
Very authentic shanghai cuisine. Great food
The waitress was really nice and welcoming, she recommended me fish noodle soup and it was mouthgasmic. She then served me complementary tapioca dessert. Would come again.

Food is prepared very freshly. Staff on hand all the time. The hot and sour soup was very tasty, so was the dumplings and shrimp wontons.  Bruce sat us and Joe served us. The warm, vegetable tilted and fried peanuts was a treat.  The place …
One of the few places on the Westside with Shanghainese pan fried buns. Delish.
Pretty good fried rice
- The service is average. - Certain items should be avoided

Service was okay. Food was a little bit too salty and greasy.

Service was non attentive and slow. Ordered their recommended pan fried boa, my favorite XiaoLongBao  and a seafood noodle. Fired Boa and noodle were salty and not edible. The XiaLongBao skin was very thick. Could not finish half of these orders.  A big disappointment for my favorite food.

First time here, hidden way surrounded by Japanese cuisine is a surprisingly authentic Shanghainese cuisine. Xiaolongbao is a must, and it was very tasty and contains very sweet and delicious soup. Other dishes we tried are also very tasty …
Sticky tables, mediocre service, food is okay
Really good place. Great food

Legitimate Chinese food just doesn't translate to west LA. Rents are too high, maybe the non-Chinese don't like real Chinese food so they have to adulterate it, or something?  I'm not sure what. But for whatever reason, even established 626 chains such as Tasty Noodle House just don't taste as good out here.
great shanghainese food with good service
Worst food. All salt no real flavor. I became sick after and threw up. Food was very poor in quality.
Good food and service!
For Shanghai flavor, here it is. And good customer service. Remember it’s Sawtelle, it’s West LA, it’s Outside Shanghai. It’s good enough.

Super delish, tons of flavor. I've been there 3 times in the last 12 days. I keep trying new stuff. They have lots of variety, very fresh, and fast, although they don't bring it all the food out at the same time, they try but fail at that so far.

(Translated by Google) Great location, service is good and warm !!! However, the taste of the food is just bad. It's completely different from real shanghai food. Also, the Chinese noodles are Japanese ramen style with Chinese sauce in it. …
Food is good, but the portion is small.

Tasty noodle house has amazing appetizers and noodle soups, but the noodle dishes can be somewhat bland. Overall, the food was tasty, and service was good given that we were there at peak dinner time.
Very close to Chinese foods I had in China.
Very good and authentic Chinese food, great service and friendly. Will definitely come back again.

Great food, & service.
